<h2 align="center">Welcome to AtFusionDB</h2> <br>
<p style="line-height:1.3em; font-size:20px; padding: 0px 5px 0px 40px;position: relative;width: 896px;margin: 0;">

Fusion transcripts are chimeric mRNAs synthesized as a result of the fusion of two distinct genes or their transcripts. Till date, this domain has been explored largely in the animal kingdom, particularly in humans. However, some reports suggest that these chimeric transcripts may play a key role in altering overall cellular physiology in plants as well.<br> <b>AtFusionDB</b> is the first database dedicated to fusion transcripts in plants. It harbors 82,969 entries of different types of fusion transcripts identified in 3,520 paired-end RNA-Seq  samples of the model plant <b><i>Arabidopsis thaliana</i></b>. This database is believed to be beneficial for exploring the complex and rarely explored domain of gene fusion and its implications in the plant kingdom.

</p>



